Achutupo Airport (IATA: ACU) is an airport serving the island town of Achutupo, in the San Blas archipelago of Panama.  The runway is located on the mainland, 0.7 kilometres (0.4 mi) southwest of the island and is reached by boat.
There is rising terrain south of the runway. North approach and departure are over the water.
The La Palma VOR (Ident: PML) is located 47.5 nautical miles (88 km) south of the airport.


